FBIS3-50962 "drlat007_c_94012" FBIS-LAT-94-007 Document Type:Daily Report 11 Jan 1994 MEXICO Chiapas Crisis Attorney General's Office Remands 8 Rebels PA1001155994 Mexico City Canal 13 Television Azteca Network in Spanish 1300 GMT 10 Jan 94 PA1001155994 Mexico City Canal 13 Television Azteca Network in Spanish 1300 GMT 10 Jan 94 Language: Spanish Article Type:BFN [From the "Good Morning From Mexico" newscast] [Text] The Attorney General's Office has taken legal action against eight rebels arrested in Chiapas. The eight rebels have said they were led by Commander Marcos, a Guatemalan, and (Jesus Meza Yaladaqui), also a Guatemalan. The arrested were remanded under the charges of homicide, infliction of injuries, criminal association, and the use of regulation weapons exclusive to the Army. The First District judge in Tuxtla Gutierrez has remanded another group of 18 rebels.
